		<h1>mb.mbfw.pro</h1>
		<h2>Mediablox Framework Prototyping System</h2>
		<p>Welcome to the Mediablox Framework Prototype Project.</p>

		<p>This is a template project for building web site prototypes using the Mediablox Framework (MBFW). This template is used to deliver static projects in blazing speed. It has a Gulp-powered build system with the following features:</p>

		<ul>
			<li>HTML templating with Nunjucks</li>
			<li>Sass compilation and prefixing</li>
			<li>JavaScript concatenation</li>
			<li>Built-in BrowserSync server</li>
			<li>JSON Datasets</li>
			<li>Pre-Populated with WP/Timber compatible fields</li>
			<li>For production builds:</li>
			<ul>
				<li>LCSS compression</li>
				<li>LJavaScript compression</li>
				<li>LImage compression</li>
			</ul>
	</ul>

	<h2>Prerequisites</h2>

	<p>To use this template, your computer needs:</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<a href="https://nodejs.org/en/">NodeJS (0.12 or greater)</a>
		</li>
		<li>
			<a href="https://git-scm.com/">Git</a>
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Installation</h2>

	<p>To set up the template, first download it with Git:</p.

<pre>
git clone https://github.com/mediablox/mb.mbfw.pro.git projectname
</pre>

Then open the folder in your command line, and install the needed dependencies:

<pre>
cd projectname
npm install
npm setup
</pre>

<p>Finally, run `npm start` to run Gulp. Your finished site will be created in a folder called `dist`, viewable at this URL:</p>

<pre>
http://localhost:3000
</pre>

<p>To create compressed, production-ready assets, run `npm run build`.</p>

